4043309057.title: Error reading response from label manager
4043309057.description: Zebra could not read the ZAPI header from the label manager
4043309057.suggestion: Wait for the error to resolve on its own. If it does not resolve, restart Zebra.

100663297.title: Failure to raise or lower privileges
100663297.description: FRR attempted to raise or lower its privileges and was unable to do so
100663297.suggestion: Ensure that you are running FRR as the frr user and that the user has sufficient privileges to properly access root privileges

4043309058.title: Label manager could not find ZAPI client
4043309058.description: Zebra was unable to find a ZAPI client matching the given protocol and instance number.
4043309058.suggestion: Ensure clients which use the label manager are properly configured and running.

100663298.title: VRF Failure on Start
100663298.description: Upon startup FRR failed to properly initialize and startup the VRF subsystem
100663298.suggestion: Ensure that there is sufficient memory to start processes and restart FRR

4043309059.title: Zebra could not relay label manager response
4043309059.description: Zebra found the client and instance to relay the label manager response or request to, but was not able to do so, possibly because the connection was closed.
4043309059.suggestion: Ensure clients which use the label manager are properly configured and running.

100663299.title: Socket Error
100663299.description: When attempting to access a socket a system error has occured and we were unable to properly complete the request
100663299.suggestion: Ensure that there are sufficient system resources available and ensure that the frr user has sufficient permisions to work.  If necessary open an Issue

100663300.title: ZAPI Error
100663300.description: A version miss-match has been detected between zebra and client protocol
100663300.suggestion: Two different versions of FRR have been installed and the install is not properly setup.  Completely stop FRR, remove it from the system and reinstall.  Typically only developers should see this issue.

4043309061.title: Mismatch between ZAPI instance and encoded message instance
4043309061.description: While relaying a request to the external label manager, Zebra noticed that the instance number encoded in the message did not match the client instance number.

100663301.title: ZAPI Error
100663301.description: The ZAPI subsystem has detected an encoding issue, between zebra and a client protocol
100663301.suggestion: Gather data and open an Issue, also Restart FRR

100663302.title: ZAPI Error
100663302.description: The ZAPI subsystem has detected a socket error between zebra and a client

100663303.title: System Call Error
100663303.description: FRR has detected a error from using a vital system call and has probably already exited
100663303.suggestion: Ensure permissions are correct for FRR files, users and groups are correct. Additionally check that sufficient system resources are available.

4043309064.title: Zebra label manager used all available labels
4043309064.description: Zebra is unable to assign additional label chunks because it has exhausted its assigned label range.
4043309064.suggestion: Make the label range bigger and restart Zebra.

100663304.title: VTY Subsystem Error
100663304.description: FRR has detected a problem with the specified configuration file
100663304.suggestion: Ensure configuration file exists and has correct permissions for operations Additionally ensure that all config lines are correct as well

4043309065.title: Daemon mismatch when releasing label chunks
4043309065.description: Zebra noticed a mismatch between a label chunk and a protocol daemon number or instance when releasing unused label chunks.

100663305.title: SNMP Subsystem Error
100663305.description: FRR has detected a problem with the snmp library it uses A callback from this subsystem has indicated some error
100663305.suggestion: Examine callback message and ensure snmp is properly setup and working

4043309066.title: Zebra did not free any label chunks
4043309066.description: Zebra's chunk cleanup procedure ran, but no label chunks were released.

100663306.title: Interface Subsystem Error
100663306.description: FRR has detected a problem with interface data from the kernel as it deviates from what we would expect to happen via normal netlink messaging
100663306.suggestion: Open an Issue with all relevant log files and restart FRR

4043309067.title: Dataplane returned invalid status code
4043309067.description: The underlying dataplane responded to a Zebra message or other interaction with an unrecognized, unknown or invalid status code.

100663307.title: NameSpace Subsystem Error
100663307.description: FRR has detected a problem with NameSpace data from the kernel as it deviates from what we would expect to happen via normal kernel messaging
100663307.suggestion: Open an Issue with all relevant log files and restart FRR

4043309068.title: A necessary work queue does not exist.
4043309068.description: A necessary work queue does not exist.

100663308.title: Developmental Escape Error
100663308.description: FRR has detected an issue where new development has not properly updated all code paths.
100663308.suggestion: Open an Issue with all relevant log files

4043309069.title: Failed to add FEC for MPLS client
4043309069.description: A client requested a label binding for a new FEC, but Zebra was unable to add the FEC to its internal table.

100663309.title: ZMQ Subsystem Error
100663309.description: FRR has detected an issue with the Zero MQ subsystem and ZeroMQ is not working properly now
100663309.suggestion: Open an Issue with all relevant log files and restart FRR

4043309070.title: Failed to remove FEC for MPLS client
4043309070.description: Zebra was unable to find and remove a FEC in its internal table.

100663310.title: Feature or system unavailable
100663310.description: FRR was not compiled with support for a particular feature, or it is not available on the current platform
100663310.suggestion: Recompile FRR with the feature enabled, or find out what platforms support the feature

4043309071.title: IRDP message length mismatch
4043309071.description: The length encoded in the IP TLV does not match the length of the packet received.

100663311.title: SNMP has discovered a warning
100663311.description: The SNMP AgentX library has returned a warning that we should report to the end user
100663311.suggestion: Gather Log data and open an Issue.

4043309072.title: Attempted to perform nexthop update for unknown address family
4043309072.description: Zebra attempted to perform a nexthop update for unknown address family

100663312.title: The stream subsystem has encountered an error
100663312.description: During sanity checking stream.c has detected an error in the data associated with a particular stream
100663312.suggestion: Gather log data and open an Issue, restart FRR

4043309073.title: Dataplane installation failure
4043309073.description: Installation of routes to underlying dataplane failed.
4043309073.suggestion: Check all configuration parameters for correctness.

100663313.title: The Linux namespace subsystem has encountered a parsing error
100663313.description: During system startup an invalid parameter for the namesapce was give to FRR
100663313.suggestion: Gather log data and open an Issue. restart FRR

4043309074.title: Dataplane deletion failure
4043309074.description: Deletion of routes from underlying dataplane failed.
4043309074.suggestion: Check all configuration parameters for correctness.

100663314.title: The Event subsystem has detected a slow process
100663314.description: The Event subsystem has detected a slow process, this typically indicates that FRR is having trouble completing work in a timely manner.  This can be either a misconfiguration, bug, or some combination therof.
100663314.suggestion: Gather log data and open an Issue

4043309075.title: Zebra table lookup failed
4043309075.description: Zebra attempted to look up a table for a particular address family and subsequent address family, but didn't find anything.
4043309075.suggestion: If you entered a command to trigger this error, make sure you entered the arguments correctly. Check your config file for any potential errors. If these look correct, seek help.

100663315.title: Reached the Route-Map Recursion Limit
100663315.description: The Route-Map subsystem has detected a route-map depth of RMAP_RECURSION_LIMIT and has stopped processing
100663315.suggestion: Re-work the Route-Map in question to not have so many route-map statements, or recompile FRR with a higher limit

4043309076.title: Netlink backend not available
4043309076.description: FRR was not compiled with support for Netlink. Any operations that require Netlink will fail.
4043309076.suggestion: Recompile FRR with Netlink, or install a package that supports this feature.

100663316.title: Unable to open configuration file
100663316.description: The config subsystem attempted to read in it's configuration file which failed, so we are falling back to the backup config file to see if it is available

4043309077.title: Protocol Buffers backend not available
4043309077.description: FRR was not compiled with support for Protocol Buffers. Any operations that require Protobuf will fail.
4043309077.suggestion: Recompile FRR with Protobuf support, or install a package that supports this feature.

100663317.title: The VRF subsystem has encountered a parsing error
100663317.description: The VRF subsystem, during initialization, has found a parsing error with input it has received
100663317.suggestion: Check the length of the vrf name and adjust accordingly

4043309078.title: Table manager used all available IDs
4043309078.description: Zebra's table manager used up all IDs available to it and can't assign any more.
4043309078.suggestion: Reconfigure Zebra with a larger range of table IDs.

4043309079.title: Daemon mismatch when releasing table chunks
4043309079.description: Zebra noticed a mismatch between a table ID chunk and a protocol daemon number instance when releasing unused table chunks.

4043309080.title: Zebra did not free any table chunks
4043309080.description: Zebra's table chunk cleanup procedure ran, but no table chunks were released.

4043309081.title: Address family specifier unrecognized
4043309081.description: Zebra attempted to process information from somewhere that included an address family specifier, but did not recognize the provided specifier.
4043309081.suggestion: Ensure that your configuration is correct. If it is, notify a developer.

4043309082.title: Incorrect protocol for table manager client
4043309082.description: Zebra's table manager only accepts connections from daemons managing dynamic routing protocols, but received a connection attempt from a daemon that does not meet this criterion.

4043309083.title: Mismatch between message and client protocol and/or instance
4043309083.description: Zebra detected a mismatch between a client's protocol and/or instance numbers versus those stored in a message transiting its socket.

4043309084.title: Label manager unable to assign label chunk
4043309084.description: Zebra's label manager was unable to assign a label chunk to client.
4043309084.suggestion: Ensure that Zebra has a sufficient label range available and that there is not a range collision.

4043309085.title: Label request from unidentified client
4043309085.description: Zebra's label manager received a label request from an unidentified client.

4043309086.title: Table manager unable to assign table chunk
4043309086.description: Zebra's table manager was unable to assign a table chunk to a client.
4043309086.suggestion: Ensure that Zebra has sufficient table ID range available and that there is not a range collision.

4043309087.title: Table request from unidentified client
4043309087.description: Zebra's table manager received a table request from an unidentified client.

4043309088.title: Cannot set receive buffer size
4043309088.description: Socket receive buffer size could not be set in the kernel

4043309089.title: Unknown Netlink message type
4043309089.description: Zebra received a Netlink message with an unrecognized type field.
4043309089.suggestion: Verify that you are running the latest version of FRR to ensure kernel compatibility. If the problem persists, notify a developer.

4043309090.title: Receive buffer overrun
4043309090.description: The kernel's buffer for a socket has been overrun, rendering the socket invalid.
4043309090.suggestion: Zebra will restart itself. Notify a developer if this issue shows up frequently.

4043309091.title: Netlink message length mismatch
4043309091.description: Zebra received a Netlink message with incorrect length fields.

4043309092.title: Received unexpected response from kernel
4043309092.description: Received unexpected response from the kernel via Netlink.

4043309093.title: Bad sequence number in Netlink message
4043309093.description: Zebra received a Netlink message with a bad sequence number.

4043309094.title: Multipath number was out of valid range
4043309094.description: Multipath number specified to Zebra must be in the appropriate range
4043309094.suggestion: Provide a multipath number that is within its accepted range

4043309095.title: String could not be parsed as IP prefix
4043309095.description: There was an attempt to parse a string as an IPv4 or IPv6 prefix, but the string could not be parsed and this operation failed.

4043309096.title: Failed to add MAC address to interface
4043309096.description: Zebra attempted to assign a MAC address to a vxlan interface but failed

4043309097.title: Failed to delete VNI
4043309097.description: Zebra attempted to delete a VNI entry and failed

4043309098.title: Adding remote VTEP failed
4043309098.description: Zebra attempted to add a remote VTEP and failed.

4043309099.title: Adding VNI failed
4043309099.description: Zebra attempted to add a VNI hash to an interface and failed

4043309100.title: Zebra failed to read namespace inotify information
4043309100.description: Zebra received an event from inotify, but failed to read what it was.

4043309101.title: Zebra label manager received malformed label request
4043309101.description: Zebra's label manager received a label request from a client whose protocol type does not match the protocol field received in the message.
4043309101.suggestion: This is a bug. Please report it.

4043309102.title: Zebra failed to install LSP into the kernel
4043309102.description: Zebra made an attempt to install a label switched path, but the kernel indicated that the installation was not successful.
4043309102.suggestion: Wait for Zebra to reattempt installation.

4043309103.title: Zebra failed to remove LSP from the kernel
4043309103.description: Zebra made an attempt to remove a label switched path, but the kernel indicated that the deletion was not successful.
4043309103.suggestion: Wait for Zebra to reattempt deletion.

4043309104.title: Zebra will not run with MPLS support
4043309104.description: Zebra noticed that the running kernel does not support MPLS, so it disabled MPLS support.
4043309104.suggestion: If you want MPLS support, upgrade the kernel to a version that provides MPLS support.

4043309105.title: A call to sysctl() failed
4043309105.description: sysctl() returned a nonzero exit code, indicating an error.
4043309105.suggestion: The log message should contain further details on the specific error that occurred; investigate the reported error.

4043309107.title: Zebra failed to create namespace VRF
4043309107.description: Zebra failed to create namespace VRF

4043309108.title: Zebra attempted to delete nonexistent namespace
4043309108.description: Zebra attempted to delete a particular namespace, but no VRF associated with that namespace could be found to delete.

4043309109.title: Zebra received ICMP packet with invalid checksum
4043309109.description: Zebra received an ICMP packet with a bad checksum and has silently ignored it.
4043309109.suggestion: If the problem continues to occur, investigate the source of the bad ICMP packets.

4043309110.title: Zebra received ICMP packet with bad type code
4043309110.description: Zebra received an ICMP packet with a bad code for the message type and has silently ignored it.
4043309110.suggestion: If the problem continues to occur, investigate the source of the bad ICMP packets.

4043309111.title: Zebra received IRDP packet while operating in wrong mode
4043309111.description: Zebra received a multicast IRDP packet while operating in unicast mode, or vice versa.
4043309111.suggestion: If you wish to receive the messages, change your IRDP settings accordingly.

4043309112.title: Zebra received IRDP packet with bad type

4043309113.title: Zebra could not find table for next hop
4043309113.description: Zebra attempted to add a next hop but could not find the appropriate table to install it in.

4043309114.title: Zebra interface listing failed
4043309114.description: Zebra encountered an error attempting to query sysctl for a list of interfaces on the system.
4043309114.suggestion: Check that Zebra is running with the appropriate permissions. If it is, please report this as a bug.

4043309115.title: Unknown message format for Zebra's FPM module
4043309115.description: Zebra's FPM module takes an argument which specifies the message format to use, but the format was either not provided or was not a valid format. The FPM interface will be disabled.
4043309115.suggestion: Provide or correct the module argument to provide a valid format. See documentation for further information.

4043309116.title: Zebra client connection failed
4043309116.description: A Zebra client encountered an I/O error and is shutting down. This can occur under normal circumstances, such as when FRR is restarting or shutting down; it can also happen if the daemon crashed. Usually this warning can be ignored.
4043309116.suggestion: Ignore this warning, it is mostly informational.

4043309117.title: Zebra failed to send message to client
4043309117.description: Zebra attempted to send a message to one of its clients, but the write operation failed. The connection will be closed.
4043309117.suggestion: Ignore this warning, it is mostly informational.

4043309118.title: Zebra received Netlink message with invalid family
4043309118.description: Zebra received a Netlink message with an invalid address family.
4043309118.suggestion: Inspect the logged address family and submit it with a bug report.

4043309119.title: Zebra tried to remove address from unknown subnet
4043309119.description: Zebra attempted to remove an address from an unknown subnet.
4043309119.suggestion: This is a bug, please report it.

4043309120.title: Zebra tried to remove unregistered address
4043309120.description: Zebra attempted to remove an address from a subnet it was not registered on.
4043309120.suggestion: This is a bug, please report it.

4043309121.title: Interface is up but PTM check has not completed
4043309121.description: Zebra noticed that an interface came up and attempted to perform its usual setup procedures, but the PTM check failed and the operation was aborted.
4043309121.suggestion: If the problem persists, ensure that the interface is actually up and that PTM is functioning properly.

4043309122.title: Kernel rejected sourcedest route
4043309122.description: Zebra attempted to install a sourcedest route into the kernel, but the kernel did not acknowledge its installation. The route is unsupported.

4043309123.title: Zebra encountered an unknown interface specifier
4043309123.description: Zebra was asked to look up an interface with a given name or index, but could not find the interface corresponding to the given name or index.

4043309124.title: Zebra could not find the specified VRF
4043309124.description: Zebra tried to look up a VRF, either by name or ID, and could not find it. This could be due to internal inconsistency (a bug) or a configuration error.
4043309124.suggestion: Check configuration values for correctness. If values are correct, please file a bug report.

4043309125.title: More nexthops were provided than the configured multipath limit
4043309125.description: A route with multiple nexthops was given, but the number of nexthops exceeded the configured multipath limit.
4043309125.suggestion: Reduce the number of nexthops, or increase the multipath limit.

4043309126.title: Zebra failed to create one or more nexthops
4043309126.description: While attempting to create nexthops for a route installation operation, Zebra found that it was unable to create one or more of the given nexthops.
4043309126.suggestion: Check configuration values for correctness. If they are correct, report this as a bug.

4043309127.title: Zebra received sourcedest route install without IPv6 address family
4043309127.description: Zebra received a message from a client requesting a sourcedest route installation, but the address family was not set to IPv6. Only IPv6 is supported for sourcedest routing.
4043309127.suggestion: This is a bug; please report it.

4043309128.title: Zebra received an installation / creation request for a pseudowire that already exists
4043309128.description: Zebra received an installation or creation request for a pseudowire that already exists, so the installation / creation has been skipped.

4043309129.title: Zebra received uninstall request for a pseudowire that doesn't exist
4043309129.description: Zebra received an uninstall request for a pseudowire that doesn't exist, so the uninstallation has been skipped.

4043309130.title: Zebra received an uninstallation / deletion request for a pseudowire that already exists
4043309130.description: Zebra received an uninstallation / deletion request for a pseudowire that doesn't exist, so the uninstallation / deletion has been skipped.

4043309131.title: No address on interface
4043309131.description: Zebra attempted to retrieve a connected address for an interface, but the interface had no connected addresses.
4043309131.suggestion: This warning is situational; it is usually informative but can indicate a misconfiguration.

4043309132.title: Zebra failed to add address to interface
4043309132.description: Zebra attempted to add an address to an interface but was unsuccessful.

4043309133.title: Zebra could not enable IRDP on interface
4043309133.description: Zebra attempted to enable IRDP on an interface, but could not create the IRDP socket. The system may be out of socket resources, or privilege elevation may have failed.
4043309133.suggestion: Verify that Zebra has the appropriate privileges and that the system has sufficient socket resources.

4043309134.title: Zebra attempted to enable IRDP on an interface, but the interface was down
4043309134.description: Zebra attempted to enable IRDP on an interface, but the interface was down.
4043309134.suggestion: Bring up the interface that IRDP is desired on.

4043309135.title: Zebra cannot enable IRDP on interface because multicast is disabled
4043309135.description: Zebra attempted to enable IRDP on an interface, but multicast functionality was not enabled on the interface.

4043309136.title: Zebra received warning message from Netlink
4043309136.description: Zebra received a warning message from Netlink
4043309136.suggestion: This message is informational. See the Netlink error message for details.

4043309137.title: Zebra could not access /var/run/netns
4043309137.description: Zebra tried to verify that the run directory for Linux network namespaces existed, but this test failed.
4043309137.suggestion: Ensure that Zebra has the proper privileges to access this directory.

4043309138.title: Zebra received unknown address family on interface
4043309138.description: Zebra received a notification of a connected prefix on an interface but did not recognize the address family as IPv4 or IPv6

4043309139.title: Zebra route has same destination address as local interface
4043309139.description: Zebra noticed that a route on an interface has the same destination address as an address on the interface itself, which may cause issues with routing protocols.
4043309139.suggestion: Investigate the source of the route to determine why the destination and interface addresses are the same.

4043309140.title: Zebra broadcast address sanity check failed
4043309140.description: Zebra computed the broadcast address for a connected prefix based on the netmask and found that it did not match the broadcast address it received for the prefix on that interface
4043309140.suggestion: Investigate the source of the broadcast address to determine why it does not match the computed address.

4043309141.title: Zebra encountered unknown address family during redistribution
4043309141.description: During a redistribution operation Zebra encountered an unknown address family.
4043309141.suggestion: This warning can be ignored; the redistribution operation will skip the unknown address family.

4043309142.title: Zebra advertising unusable interface address
4043309142.description: Zebra is advertising an address on an interface that is not yet fully installed on the interface.
4043309142.suggestion: This message is informational. The address should show up on the interface shortly after advertisement.

4043309143.title: Zebra received route advertisement with parameter mismatch
4043309143.description: Zebra received a router advertisement, but one of the non-critical parameters (AdvCurHopLimit, AdvManagedFlag, AdvOtherConfigFlag, AdvReachableTime or AdvRetransTimer) does not match Zebra's local settings.
4043309143.suggestion: This message is informational; the route advertisement will be processed as normal. If issues arise due to the parameter mismatch, check Zebra's router advertisement configuration.

4043309144.title: Zebra received kernel message with uknown version
4043309144.description: Zebra received a message from the kernel with a message version that does not match Zebra's internal version. Depending on version compatibility, this may cause issues sending and receiving messages to the kernel.
4043309144.suggestion: If issues arise, check if there is a version of FRR available for your kernel version.

4043309145.title: Zebra could not determine proper gateway for kernel route
4043309145.description: Zebra attempted to install a route into the kernel, but noticed it had no gateway and no interface with a gateway could be located.

4043309146.title: Zebra exceeded maximum LSP labels for a single rtmsg
4043309146.description: Zebra attempted to push more than one label into the kernel; the maximum on OpenBSD is 1 label.

4043309147.title: EVPN MAC already learnt as remote sticky MAC
4043309147.description: Zebra tried to handle a local MAC addition but noticed that it had already learnt the MAC from a remote peer.

4043309148.title: Kernel does not support IPv6 sourcedest routes
4043309148.description: Zebra attempted to install a sourcedest route into the kernel, but IPv6 sourcedest routes are not supported on the current kernel.
4043309148.suggestion: Do not use v6 sourcedest routes, or upgrade your kernel.

4043309149.title: EVPN MAC is detected duplicate
4043309149.description: Zebra has hit duplicate address detection threshold which means host MAC is moving.
4043309149.suggestion: Check network topology to detect duplicate host MAC for correctness.

4043309150.title: EVPN IP is detected duplicate by MAC
4043309150.description: Zebra has hit duplicate address detection threshold which means MAC-IP pair is moving.
4043309150.suggestion: Check network topology to detect duplicate host MAC for correctness.

4043309151.title: EVPN IP is detected duplicate
4043309151.description: Zebra has hit duplicate address detection threshold which means host IP is moving.
4043309151.suggestion: Check network topology to detect duplicate host IP for correctness.

134217729.title: Failure to process a packet
134217729.description: OSPF attempted to process a received packet but could not
134217729.suggestion: Most likely a bug. If the problem persists, report the problem for troubleshooting

134217730.title: Failure to process Router LSA
134217730.description: OSPF attempted to process a Router LSA but Advertising ID mismatch with link id
134217730.suggestion: Check OSPF network config for any config issue, If the problem persists, report the problem for troubleshooting

134217731.title: OSPF Domain Corruption
134217731.description: OSPF attempted to process a Router LSA but Advertising ID mismatch with link id
134217731.suggestion: Check OSPF network Database for corrupted LSA, If the problem persists, shutdown OSPF domain and report the problem for troubleshooting

134217732.title: OSPF Initialization failure
134217732.description: OSPF failed to initialized OSPF default insance
134217732.suggestion: Ensure there is adequate memory on the device. If the problem persists, report the problem for troubleshooting

134217733.title: OSPF SR Invalid DB
134217733.description: OSPF Segment Routing Database is invalid
134217733.suggestion: Most likely a bug. If the problem persists, report the problem for troubleshooting

134217734.title: OSPF SR hash node creation failed
134217734.description: OSPF Segment Routing node creation failed
134217734.suggestion: Most likely a bug. If the problem persists, report the problem for troubleshooting

134217735.title: OSPF SR Invalid LSA ID
134217735.description: OSPF Segment Routing invalid lsa id
134217735.suggestion: Restart OSPF instance, If the problem persists, report the problem for troubleshooting

134217736.title: OSPF SR Invalid Algorithm
134217736.suggestion: Most likely a bug. If the problem persists, report the problem for troubleshooting

134217737.title: OSPF FSM invalid state detected
134217737.description: OSPF has attempted to change states when it should not be able to
134217737.suggestion: Gather log files and open an issue

134217738.title: OSPF Encountered a Large Hello
134217738.description: OSPF attempted to send a Hello larger than MTU but did not
134217738.suggestion: Too many neighbors configured on a single interface. Suggestion is to decrease the number of neighbors on a single interface/subnet

134217739.title: OSPF does not support `set metric +rtt/-rtt`
134217739.description: This implementation of OSPF does not currently support `set metric +rtt/-rtt`
134217739.suggestion: Do not use this particular set command for an ospf route-map

134217740.title: OSPF has noticed a MD5 issue
134217740.description: Something has gone wrong with the calculation of the MD5 data
134217740.suggestion: Ensure your key is correct, gather log data from this side as well as peer and open an Issue

134217741.title: OSPF has detected packet information missmatch
134217741.description: OSPF has detected that packet information received is incorrect
134217741.suggestion: Ensure interface configuration is correct, gather log files from here and the peer and open an Issue

134217742.title: OSPF has determined that a LSA packet will be too large
134217742.description: OSPF has received data that is causing it to recalculate how large packets should be and has discovered that the packet size needed would be too large and we will need to fragment packets
134217742.suggestion: Further divide up your network with areas

134217743.title: OSPF has received a LSA-type that it was not expecting
134217743.description: OSPF has received a LSA-type that it was not expecting during processing

To remedy this, after performing collision detection and resolution the peer session has been reset in order to apply the new configuration.
